VOIP Directory — MySQL Fix Instructions
========================================

PROBLEM: Node.js hangs when connecting to MySQL 8.0 over TCP.
CAUSE:   MySQL 8.0 root user uses caching_sha2_password which requires SSL.
         mysql2 connects without SSL and stalls.

─────────────────────────────────────────
STEP 1 — Run in MySQL Workbench
─────────────────────────────────────────

NOTE: MySQL treats 'localhost' and '127.0.0.1' as DIFFERENT hosts.
      Node.js connects via 127.0.0.1 (TCP), so the user must exist for that host.

-- Create user for BOTH localhost and 127.0.0.1:
CREATE USER IF NOT EXISTS 'voipapp'@'localhost'  IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'Cityvoip@502';
CREATE USER IF NOT EXISTS 'voipapp'@'127.0.0.1' IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'Cityvoip@502';

GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON bcc_voip_directory.* TO 'voipapp'@'localhost';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON bcc_voip_directory.* TO 'voipapp'@'127.0.0.1';

-- Also fix root for 127.0.0.1:
CREATE USER IF NOT EXISTS 'root'@'127.0.0.1' IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'Cityvoip@502';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON *.* TO 'root'@'127.0.0.1' WITH GRANT OPTION;

FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

-- Verify all entries (share this output if still failing):
SELECT user, host, plugin FROM mysql.user WHERE user IN ('root', 'voipapp');


─────────────────────────────────────────
STEP 1b — Fix MySQL global auth plugin (my.ini)
─────────────────────────────────────────

REASON: Even with per-user mysql_native_password, MySQL 8.0 still initiates
        handshakes with caching_sha2_password globally. mysql2 cannot complete
        this without SSL and hangs. Changing the global default fixes it.

-- Find my.ini location (run in PowerShell):
Get-ChildItem "C:\ProgramData\MySQL\" -Recurse -Filter "my.ini" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
Get-ChildItem "C:\Program Files\MySQL\" -Recurse -Filter "my.ini" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

-- Open my.ini and add this line under [mysqld]:
[mysqld]
default_authentication_plugin=mysql_native_password

-- Restart MySQL service (PowerShell as Admin):
Restart-Service -Name "MySQL80"

-- Verify MySQL restarted:
Get-Service -Name "MySQL80"


─────────────────────────────────────────
STEP 2 — Update .env on the server (PowerShell as Admin)
─────────────────────────────────────────

@"
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_USER=voipapp
DB_PASSWORD=Cityvoip@502
DB_NAME=bcc_voip_directory
PORT=5001
"@ | Out-File -FilePath "C:\inetpub\wwwroot\VOIP-Directory\backend\.env" -Encoding utf8


─────────────────────────────────────────
